TIYESE JERANJI Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories About 25 people have been left homeless after a fire gutted their shacks in Vrygrond&nbsp; today (Monday 6 March). &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; Tracy Whitaker, fire and rescue services assistant media spokesperson says, the City's Fire and Rescue Service responded to wood and iron structures burning in Philemon Road - Vrygrond at &nbsp;16:15. &ldquo;There are about 10 wood and iron structures alight and 25 people have been displaced. Three fire fighting cars with 15 permanent firefighters are currently on scene. The cause of the fire is undetermined at this stage.&rdquo; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.